The paper deals with automata and regular expressions, which are fundamental concepts in formal language theory (cs.FL). The focus is on weighted versions of these structures, which suggests a connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses training methods for learning weights, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions the efficient computation of inside weights, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
